BEGIN_PGML

Consider an LTI system whose input [`x[n]`] and output [`y[n]`] are related by the difference equation [`y[n-1] + \frac{[$numer2]}{[$denom]}y[n] + \frac{[$numer*$q]}{[$denom]}y[n+1] = x[n]`]. Determine the three possible choices for the impulse response that makes this system 1) causal, 2) non-causal and 3) anti-causal. Then for each case, determine if the system is stable or not.

END_PGML

